1
00:00:32,240 --> 00:00:36,953
THE PRACTICAL GUIDE TO LOVE

2
00:00:38,079 --> 00:00:39,705
What is...

3
00:00:39,997 --> 00:00:42,124
going on?

4
00:00:42,208 --> 00:00:45,461
Oh, I...

5
00:00:53,427 --> 00:00:57,265
We just look like a couple
in their talking stage

6
00:00:57,348 --> 00:00:59,433
having spent the night together.

7
00:01:01,686 --> 00:01:03,938
But why is he there?

8
00:01:04,021 --> 00:01:06,732
Oh! I went out for some fresh air.

9
00:01:07,525 --> 00:01:09,860
Oh, right! Right by the cafe.

10
00:01:09,944 --> 00:01:12,905
We said we'd go
for a second round of drinks, right?

11
00:01:12,989 --> 00:01:14,031
Are you guys detectives?

12
00:01:14,115 --> 00:01:16,784
You think going over what happened
will get you anywhere?

13
00:01:25,668 --> 00:01:26,711
Be careful!

14
00:01:26,794 --> 00:01:27,878
Watch your step!

15
00:01:27,962 --> 00:01:30,715
One, two!

16
00:01:30,965 --> 00:01:31,966
We’re almost there.

17
00:01:32,800 --> 00:01:34,010
Wait!

18
00:01:35,094 --> 00:01:36,137
Oh, gosh.

19
00:01:36,304 --> 00:01:38,431
Are you kidding me?

20
00:01:38,598 --> 00:01:40,141
Should I just leave him here?

21
00:01:40,224 --> 00:01:42,184
No, don't leave without me.

22
00:01:42,268 --> 00:01:44,937
You're like a puppy
with separation anxiety.

23
00:01:45,146 --> 00:01:46,772
One, two, three!

24
00:01:50,067 --> 00:01:52,612
- Ui-yeong!
- Hey, Ji-su.

25
00:01:52,862 --> 00:01:56,407
What are you doing here?
Weren't you at the cafe? What?

26
00:01:56,490 --> 00:01:58,159
I left something at the hotel.

27
00:01:58,242 --> 00:01:59,327
I see.

28
00:01:59,410 --> 00:02:01,662
Excuse me! Why are you sleeping
on her shoulder? Hey!

29
00:02:01,746 --> 00:02:03,372
I'll take him to the hotel.

30
00:02:03,456 --> 00:02:05,791
You're going to the hotel like that?

31
00:02:05,875 --> 00:02:07,001
- Let's go.
- Huh?

32
00:02:07,084 --> 00:02:08,794
Come. Unless you want to sleep here.

33
00:02:08,878 --> 00:02:10,212
- Gosh!
- Wait!

34
00:02:10,296 --> 00:02:12,214
- What a mess.
- Let's go.

35
00:02:22,558 --> 00:02:24,852
- Oh, gosh.
- Man!

36
00:02:33,694 --> 00:02:34,945
I'm thirsty...

37
00:02:35,404 --> 00:02:37,907
Please give me some water, sir.

38
00:02:38,824 --> 00:02:40,242
You're kidding.

39
00:02:43,287 --> 00:02:45,581
Seriously.

40
00:02:54,090 --> 00:02:55,091
Here.

41
00:03:13,275 --> 00:03:15,194
- Cold!
- Are you serious?

42
00:03:15,277 --> 00:03:16,737
You're a handful.

43
00:03:16,904 --> 00:03:18,280
It's cold.

44
00:03:29,041 --> 00:03:30,376
Let's go, Ui-yeong.

45
00:03:34,964 --> 00:03:35,965
Are you sleeping?

46
00:03:38,008 --> 00:03:39,135
This...

47
00:03:40,386 --> 00:03:41,762
isn't right.

48
00:03:59,280 --> 00:04:00,281
Gosh.

49
00:04:10,124 --> 00:04:11,459
That hurts.

50
00:04:36,776 --> 00:04:38,486
The drinks really got to her head, huh?

51
00:05:06,889 --> 00:05:09,892
There's no way
I can leave these two alone.

52
00:06:04,864 --> 00:06:08,200
THE PRACTICAL GUIDE TO LOVE
EPISODE 6

53
00:06:10,578 --> 00:06:13,080
I'm sorry, you couldn't even go home
because of me.

54
00:06:13,163 --> 00:06:14,540
It's fine. I'm okay.

55
00:06:14,623 --> 00:06:15,624
What do you mean?

56
00:06:15,958 --> 00:06:18,294
You can't just trust some guy
and go to his hotel room!

57
00:06:19,128 --> 00:06:20,713
What would you have done without me?

58
00:06:20,796 --> 00:06:23,215
I understand I owe you one

59
00:06:23,299 --> 00:06:24,550
but I'm not the type

60
00:06:24,633 --> 00:06:26,844
to cross boundaries
just because I'm drunk.

61
00:06:27,428 --> 00:06:30,514
How do you know your drunk habits
when you don't know when you get drunk?

62
00:06:30,598 --> 00:06:32,808
I almost thought
you were a freshman at a party.

63
00:06:32,975 --> 00:06:34,018
A freshman?

64
00:06:34,602 --> 00:06:36,979
Cut it out.
You're making him uncomfortable.

65
00:06:37,229 --> 00:06:40,316
- And nothing happened. It's fine.
- Are you serious?

66
00:06:42,860 --> 00:06:46,864
I'd better go
before people start showing up for work.

67
00:06:46,989 --> 00:06:48,282
Take a shower first.

68
00:06:48,490 --> 00:06:50,284
- You slept with him, after all.
- Hey!

69
00:06:52,369 --> 00:06:55,289
We have a great shower room for employees.

70
00:06:55,831 --> 00:06:57,791
Okay, go before people see you.

71
00:06:57,875 --> 00:06:58,918
Okay, then.

72
00:06:59,251 --> 00:07:00,294
Oh, wait.

73
00:07:01,128 --> 00:07:03,672
Oh, right. Thanks.

74
00:07:03,964 --> 00:07:05,382
I'm so sorry. I feel terrible.

75
00:07:05,466 --> 00:07:07,760
Why don't we grab dinner this weekend?

76
00:07:07,843 --> 00:07:09,261
Get whatever you want. My treat.

77
00:07:09,345 --> 00:07:10,387
Oh...

78
00:07:11,180 --> 00:07:12,181
Sure, then.

79
00:07:12,431 --> 00:07:14,892
How about Saturday?

80
00:07:15,351 --> 00:07:16,685
Sure, a dinner sounds great.

81
00:07:17,061 --> 00:07:20,272
You owe me dinner, too.
You owe me a big one.

82
00:07:20,356 --> 00:07:21,774
No, you owe me many big ones.

83
00:07:21,857 --> 00:07:23,651
I already told you I would.

84
00:07:24,526 --> 00:07:27,071
Let's decide when to meet over text.

85
00:07:27,154 --> 00:07:28,572
Okay, have a good day at work.

86
00:07:28,656 --> 00:07:29,698
Thanks.

87
00:07:29,949 --> 00:07:30,950
Bye.

88
00:07:31,742 --> 00:07:32,743
Bye.

89
00:07:38,749 --> 00:07:41,877
Are you seriously crazy?
What if someone saw you?

90
00:07:41,961 --> 00:07:43,295
My gosh!

91
00:08:01,105 --> 00:08:02,106
Hold on.

92
00:08:04,024 --> 00:08:05,275
This is too peaceful.

93
00:08:12,992 --> 00:08:15,536
She never caused any trouble
in her twenties.

94
00:08:17,621 --> 00:08:18,789
What is she doing?

95
00:08:21,166 --> 00:08:23,460
I wasted way too much energy
from the morning.

96
00:08:25,170 --> 00:08:26,547
Maybe I should get some coffee.

97
00:08:28,590 --> 00:08:29,591
What's this?

98
00:08:32,261 --> 00:08:33,595
THE MAGIC OF A SURPRISE GIFT FOR YOU

99
00:08:33,679 --> 00:08:35,097
WHO WANTS TO GO HOME
FIRST THING IN THE MORNING! - HYUN-MIN

100
00:08:39,601 --> 00:08:41,729
Hyun-min's so cute sometimes.

101
00:09:10,841 --> 00:09:12,509
Where are you, Ui-yeong?

102
00:09:12,634 --> 00:09:14,136
Didn't I say it was common courtesy

103
00:09:14,219 --> 00:09:16,472
to tell your rommate
if you weren't coming home?

104
00:09:16,805 --> 00:09:19,683
I'm calling the cops
if you don't answer by 9 a.m.

105
00:09:20,225 --> 00:09:21,477
WE HAD A STAFF PARTY

106
00:09:21,560 --> 00:09:23,812
We had a staff party to celebrate
the new event

107
00:09:24,021 --> 00:09:26,273
and it ended late,
so I just slept in the staff room.

108
00:09:26,815 --> 00:09:27,900
Sorry.

109
00:10:06,605 --> 00:10:07,731
That's my towel.

110
00:10:12,694 --> 00:10:15,864
So, did you watch us two all night?

111
00:10:16,532 --> 00:10:18,534
Don't you think that's a bit much?

112
00:10:18,617 --> 00:10:21,995
You know what's a bit much?
You sleeping on Ui-yeong's shoulder.

113
00:10:23,455 --> 00:10:25,249
How can a man be so weak to alcohol?

114
00:10:25,332 --> 00:10:26,834
Don't try to change the topic.

115
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:30,003
I don't like
how you keep hanging around Ui-yeong.

116
00:10:30,087 --> 00:10:32,673
You pretend to care,
but you just want a chance with her.

117
00:10:32,798 --> 00:10:34,133
Hanging around her?

118
00:10:34,967 --> 00:10:36,635
You look like a virgin.

119
00:10:37,094 --> 00:10:38,720
Do you even know how to get a chance?

120
00:10:38,804 --> 00:10:39,888
A virgin?

121
00:10:48,981 --> 00:10:50,357
Hey.

122
00:10:55,362 --> 00:10:56,780
- Huh?
- Oh!

123
00:10:56,864 --> 00:10:58,532
Oh, this isn't what you think it is.

124
00:10:58,615 --> 00:11:00,325
I saw nothing.

125
00:11:00,701 --> 00:11:02,703
No need to explain your private life.

126
00:11:03,287 --> 00:11:04,705
No, please let me.

127
00:11:04,788 --> 00:11:06,623
Wait! There's been a misunderstanding!

128
00:11:07,916 --> 00:11:08,959
Gosh.

129
00:11:15,299 --> 00:11:18,343
Everyone knows everything around here.

130
00:11:19,511 --> 00:11:21,263
. According to the witnesses

131
00:11:21,346 --> 00:11:25,517
there wasn't just one man, but two!

132
00:11:25,809 --> 00:11:28,604
I'm a little disappointed.

133
00:11:28,687 --> 00:11:31,481
- Why?
- You can't date multiple people

134
00:11:31,565 --> 00:11:32,816
if you're really in love.

135
00:11:32,900 --> 00:11:35,986
No, you can be in love and still have fun!

136
00:11:36,153 --> 00:11:37,821
Listen, Sae-byeok.

137
00:11:37,905 --> 00:11:40,616
Our society is too close-minded
and old-fashioned.

138
00:11:40,699 --> 00:11:43,076
They either think it's love or an affair.

139
00:11:43,285 --> 00:11:45,579
That's why people get busted
while secretly cheating

140
00:11:45,662 --> 00:11:48,749
embarrass themselves,
and ruin their careers!

141
00:11:49,166 --> 00:11:50,375
Ui-yeong!

142
00:11:50,459 --> 00:11:52,169
How long have you been there?

143
00:11:52,461 --> 00:11:54,171
Oh, I just came in.

144
00:11:55,422 --> 00:11:56,715
But...

145
00:11:57,466 --> 00:11:59,426
don't you think that's a bit harsh?

146
00:12:00,260 --> 00:12:03,764
Oh, I guess you don't believe rumors?

147
00:12:03,847 --> 00:12:06,725
Hmm? What rumor?

148
00:12:07,935 --> 00:12:12,314
"Despite being in her fifties,
Ms. S is still the queen of romance.

149
00:12:12,856 --> 00:12:14,942
She always says she's in love with acting

150
00:12:15,025 --> 00:12:17,611
but in fact, she's been head-over-heels
for someone lately!

151
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:22,115
She's in a common-law relationship
with a surgeon who used to be married

152
00:12:22,199 --> 00:12:24,660
but has an affair with Mr. B,
a director, at a hotel

153
00:12:24,743 --> 00:12:26,370
while being a sugar mommy to a model.

154
00:12:26,453 --> 00:12:30,249
The scandal is only growing
with her complicated dating life."

155
00:12:30,666 --> 00:12:32,584
The queen of romance?

156
00:12:33,293 --> 00:12:34,461
Could that be Son Jeong-a?

157
00:12:34,544 --> 00:12:37,047
It's pretty clear that it's her.

158
00:12:37,130 --> 00:12:39,716
She recently checked into our hotel.

159
00:12:39,925 --> 00:12:41,009
Really?

160
00:12:41,635 --> 00:12:44,554
This hotel is
where she meets the director.

161
00:12:56,525 --> 00:13:01,238
Mr. Jin says
he can't come to the meeting today.

162
00:13:01,363 --> 00:13:04,241
He just married his wife.
He doesn't want her to get the wrong idea.

163
00:13:05,575 --> 00:13:07,369
Is he only not coming today

164
00:13:07,536 --> 00:13:09,121
or does he want me out of his movie?

165
00:13:09,204 --> 00:13:10,789
Well...

166
00:13:11,456 --> 00:13:12,499
What a wimp.

167
00:13:13,750 --> 00:13:15,836
Sure, whatever.
Let's just grab dinner and go.

168
00:13:15,919 --> 00:13:17,796
- You can sit.
- Okay.

169
00:13:22,342 --> 00:13:25,178
Hello, I'm Kim Min-seong from Star A.

170
00:13:26,596 --> 00:13:29,224
Why haven't you denied the rumor yet?

171
00:13:29,808 --> 00:13:32,352
I don't want to add fuel to the fire
by being so rash.

172
00:13:32,769 --> 00:13:34,187
I'll explain myself soon.

173
00:13:34,438 --> 00:13:36,690
You shouldn't be following me
in my personal time.

174
00:13:36,773 --> 00:13:39,276
- This is inappropriate.
- I'll sort it...

175
00:13:39,776 --> 00:13:41,737
Hey! Don't you dare...

176
00:13:43,739 --> 00:13:45,365
Dong-hoon!

177
00:13:45,907 --> 00:13:47,784
could you please call the ambulance?

178
00:13:48,118 --> 00:13:50,203
Here, you see a larva.

179
00:13:50,287 --> 00:13:53,915
Follow the larva's outer layer,
which has been shed

180
00:13:53,999 --> 00:13:56,793
and you'll find the larva in its pupa form

181
00:13:56,877 --> 00:14:00,505
wrapped in his big blanket.

182
00:14:00,881 --> 00:14:03,258
Stop it.

183
00:14:03,342 --> 00:14:05,844
The pupae is finally coming out!

184
00:14:06,636 --> 00:14:09,139
Am I going to be okay?

185
00:14:09,222 --> 00:14:11,600
I think
my autonomic nervous system is broken.

186
00:14:12,601 --> 00:14:13,602
Come out.

187
00:14:18,482 --> 00:14:19,733
Hot!

188
00:14:21,443 --> 00:14:22,861
I'VE NEVER SEEN MR. SONG LIKE THIS

189
00:14:25,530 --> 00:14:27,407
It's not just your first hangover.

190
00:14:27,491 --> 00:14:29,409
It's also your first time
waking up with one.

191
00:14:31,995 --> 00:14:34,164
I have no right to say anything
if she rejects me.

192
00:14:34,247 --> 00:14:35,707
I must've been out of my mind.

193
00:14:35,791 --> 00:14:38,001
I should be doing my best to impress her.

194
00:14:38,085 --> 00:14:39,920
Why did I drink when I know I can't?

195
00:14:40,003 --> 00:14:41,880
It's already too late.

196
00:14:41,963 --> 00:14:43,799
But she was drunk with you.

197
00:14:44,299 --> 00:14:47,010
I'm sure she's worried
about the same thing. Don't worry.

198
00:14:47,969 --> 00:14:49,429
Gosh, you're wasting so much food!

199
00:14:49,513 --> 00:14:52,599
How can you not touch anything

200
00:14:52,682 --> 00:14:54,351
your mom makes for you?

201
00:14:56,144 --> 00:14:57,813
Aren't you seeing her on Saturday?

202
00:14:58,355 --> 00:14:59,731
That's great.

203
00:15:00,649 --> 00:15:02,442
Out with the old love, in with the new.

204
00:15:02,526 --> 00:15:04,403
Forget the hangover with some soup

205
00:15:04,528 --> 00:15:07,114
and make new memories
to forget about the old ones.

206
00:15:09,032 --> 00:15:10,033
This is perfect.

207
00:15:11,493 --> 00:15:12,619
So, what's the plan?

208
00:15:13,537 --> 00:15:16,081
We'll get some good food

209
00:15:16,456 --> 00:15:18,417
and watch the movie
we didn't watch last time.

210
00:15:18,959 --> 00:15:20,752
It's all sorted, then!

211
00:15:20,836 --> 00:15:22,921
What do you mean?
I have to start planning now.

212
00:15:24,673 --> 00:15:27,592
I have to make sure
I make up for my drunk mess.

213
00:15:29,845 --> 00:15:31,138
Hello!

214
00:15:32,347 --> 00:15:35,600
Ms. Son Jeong-a will come here today.

215
00:15:35,684 --> 00:15:37,352
Stay tuned for updates.

216
00:15:37,727 --> 00:15:41,231
There are so many reporters here.

217
00:15:42,274 --> 00:15:44,860
Man, this is a disaster.

218
00:15:44,943 --> 00:15:46,528
I'll make sure to get good updates!

219
00:15:47,279 --> 00:15:48,947
I guess I won't be going home anytime.

220
00:15:49,030 --> 00:15:51,825
Why is the security so bad
when the condo's so expensive?

221
00:15:51,908 --> 00:15:53,743
Too many celebrities live there.

222
00:15:55,620 --> 00:15:57,122
I can't drive you around

223
00:15:57,330 --> 00:15:59,458
with my leg like this.

224
00:15:59,541 --> 00:16:01,501
You should just stay here for a bit.

225
00:16:03,336 --> 00:16:06,339
It's trendy to prepare what to say
and all supporting documents

226
00:16:06,423 --> 00:16:10,427
for one big press release these days.

227
00:16:11,720 --> 00:16:12,762
Sure.

228
00:16:13,346 --> 00:16:15,140
That's better than wasting all my time

229
00:16:15,223 --> 00:16:17,100
answering trashy reporters everywhere.

230
00:16:17,184 --> 00:16:18,727
I'm not young anymore.

231
00:16:18,810 --> 00:16:20,103
I have nothing to lose.

232
00:16:21,813 --> 00:16:24,357
Just find me a reporter
who will write a good article for me.

233
00:16:24,774 --> 00:16:28,236
To beat a romance scandal
with greater love?

234
00:16:29,237 --> 00:16:30,489
You're a genius.

235
00:16:30,572 --> 00:16:33,950
You're sure no reporters can enter here,
right?

236
00:16:34,034 --> 00:16:35,118
Don't worry.

237
00:16:36,244 --> 00:16:37,829
Have you...

238
00:16:38,413 --> 00:16:42,167
ever used
the Guest Relations Officer service?

239
00:16:42,959 --> 00:16:44,961
No, what's that?

240
00:16:45,045 --> 00:16:46,254
Simply put

241
00:16:46,963 --> 00:16:49,925
it's a manager who will help you
with your stay here.

242
00:16:50,008 --> 00:16:52,093
You'll be assigned one manager

243
00:16:52,177 --> 00:16:55,764
to help you around
and get things for you. What do you think?

244
00:16:55,847 --> 00:16:57,807
Oh! That sounds great!

245
00:16:58,308 --> 00:17:00,477
Please choose a sharp female manager.

246
00:17:00,560 --> 00:17:02,062
Okay, I'll look for one.

247
00:17:03,104 --> 00:17:04,105
Enjoy your stay.

248
00:17:09,986 --> 00:17:11,571
Can you believe it?

249
00:17:11,988 --> 00:17:13,073
Did you see that article?

250
00:17:13,156 --> 00:17:14,491
LIST OF FINALISTS
FOR THE HOSPITAL DIRECTOR POSITION

251
00:17:14,574 --> 00:17:16,326
DR. SHIN JI-HUN OF SURGERY,
BORN IN 1968 (AGE 57)

252
00:17:18,787 --> 00:17:20,539
HANKUK UNIVERSITY HOSPITAL

253
00:17:20,622 --> 00:17:23,458
You've been the talk of the town
all day today

254
00:17:23,542 --> 00:17:24,960
and look! Speak of the devil.

255
00:17:25,043 --> 00:17:28,088
I didn't think you'd be on celebrity news
instead of research news.

256
00:17:29,130 --> 00:17:30,966
- Is that so?
- I'm happy

257
00:17:31,049 --> 00:17:34,219
just to be
the Vice Director of the hospital

258
00:17:34,302 --> 00:17:35,887
but everyone's been asking me

259
00:17:35,971 --> 00:17:39,975
to run for Director
for the hospital's reputation.

260
00:17:40,058 --> 00:17:43,853
I was wondering why, but now I know.

261
00:17:45,605 --> 00:17:48,692
I guess gossping is fun.

262
00:17:48,775 --> 00:17:51,861
Aren't you busy?
I didn't think you'd have time to gossip

263
00:17:52,404 --> 00:17:56,032
right in the hallway,
chatting it up like a teenageer.

264
00:17:56,992 --> 00:17:58,743
Looks like you're having fun.

265
00:18:00,620 --> 00:18:02,622
I have a surgery, so please excuse me.

266
00:18:06,042 --> 00:18:07,335
The door is closing.

267
00:18:13,425 --> 00:18:17,596
SON JEONG-A

268
00:18:23,977 --> 00:18:25,812
Did your check-in go smoothly?

269
00:18:26,771 --> 00:18:27,981
I saw the news.

270
00:18:28,732 --> 00:18:29,941
It's okay.

271
00:18:30,692 --> 00:18:34,779
I didn't think it'd be easy to date
such a big star, anyway.

272
00:18:35,780 --> 00:18:37,782
Should I meet you at the hotel
this weekend?

273
00:19:10,273 --> 00:19:12,317
Hey, Mom. You didn't have dinner, right?

274
00:19:17,113 --> 00:19:18,323
What's all this?

275
00:19:18,657 --> 00:19:19,658
Ta-da!

276
00:19:22,452 --> 00:19:23,578
It looks delicious.

277
00:19:29,084 --> 00:19:30,543
Doesn't it taste amazing?

278
00:19:31,211 --> 00:19:33,630
I know you're an adult, but sleep at home.

279
00:19:33,713 --> 00:19:36,132
I'll change the door password
if you stay out again.

280
00:19:36,675 --> 00:19:39,052
Don't say it like that.

281
00:19:39,135 --> 00:19:42,013
Just tell me you were worried about me.
And say it nicely.

282
00:19:42,222 --> 00:19:44,557
The balcony stinks
because of the big pile of recycling.

283
00:19:44,641 --> 00:19:46,267
And we're out of clean towels.

284
00:19:46,351 --> 00:19:47,727
And eggs!

285
00:19:47,811 --> 00:19:49,354
You just want me to do the chores.

286
00:19:49,437 --> 00:19:51,690
I just took out the recycling
and cleaned the floor!

287
00:19:51,773 --> 00:19:52,774
And stop drinking.

288
00:19:52,857 --> 00:19:56,277
You used to come home after a night out,
no matter how drunk you were.

289
00:19:56,361 --> 00:19:57,570
Right? I was so good.

290
00:19:57,654 --> 00:19:59,447
I always make sure to come home, so why...

291
00:20:03,993 --> 00:20:05,370
You can't go.

292
00:20:08,164 --> 00:20:09,749
What's wrong? You're scaring me.

293
00:20:15,380 --> 00:20:16,756
- Huh?
- What?

294
00:20:16,840 --> 00:20:18,007
- Huh?
- Huh?

295
00:20:18,258 --> 00:20:19,634
- Huh?
- Hmm?

296
00:20:23,555 --> 00:20:26,057
Looks like your memory's back.

297
00:20:38,653 --> 00:20:40,029
It already smells amazing.

298
00:20:41,656 --> 00:20:42,907
- Right?
- Yeah.

299
00:20:43,825 --> 00:20:45,410
- Thank you.
- Anytime.

300
00:20:46,953 --> 00:20:47,996
So

301
00:20:48,538 --> 00:20:49,539
I want you

302
00:20:50,248 --> 00:20:54,419
to be the Guest Relations Officer
for Ms. Son.

303
00:20:54,878 --> 00:20:58,590
Isn't that for the Concierge Team?

304
00:20:58,715 --> 00:21:02,135
As you know, we don't have a manual
for the position.

305
00:21:02,343 --> 00:21:05,430
So, all you have to do is
build a good rapport

306
00:21:05,513 --> 00:21:08,057
and provide the best service possible.

307
00:21:08,641 --> 00:21:12,103
I'm not sure if I'll be good.

308
00:21:13,271 --> 00:21:15,190
You know what I always say.

309
00:21:15,482 --> 00:21:19,152
The best kind of service
doesn't come from expertise.

310
00:21:19,235 --> 00:21:20,987
It comes from the heart.

311
00:21:23,239 --> 00:21:24,574
You'll do great.

312
00:21:26,493 --> 00:21:29,746
Buying things for her is your main task

313
00:21:29,829 --> 00:21:31,289
but more importantly

314
00:21:32,040 --> 00:21:35,752
the public is too cold toward her.

315
00:21:35,835 --> 00:21:37,378
And you're her fan.

316
00:21:37,921 --> 00:21:41,299
I thought it'd be nice for her
to be around someone who likes her.

317
00:21:41,549 --> 00:21:42,592
I see.

318
00:21:42,884 --> 00:21:45,470
You can fangirl in person.

319
00:21:48,223 --> 00:21:49,766
Okay, got it.

320
00:21:49,849 --> 00:21:51,226
Great.

321
00:21:51,559 --> 00:21:53,394
I'll set up the basics

322
00:21:53,478 --> 00:21:57,899
but ask her what else she needs
and get them for her.

323
00:21:58,107 --> 00:21:59,859
- Yes, sir.
- If you have any questions

324
00:22:00,527 --> 00:22:04,280
call the manager.
This is his business card.

325
00:22:08,326 --> 00:22:09,327
But remember

326
00:22:10,036 --> 00:22:12,914
work is work.

327
00:22:13,665 --> 00:22:15,166
Oh, yeah, of course.

328
00:22:16,084 --> 00:22:17,085
Sure.

329
00:22:29,264 --> 00:22:31,099
"EVERY PRODUCTION IS LIKE HER LAST
FOR THE ROMANCE QUEEN OF 20 YEARS"

330
00:22:31,850 --> 00:22:33,059
JEONG-A IS BACK ON SCREEN
AFTER A LONG BREAK WITH THE NEW MOVIE

331
00:22:37,313 --> 00:22:38,815
I'M A BIG READER LIKE SEON-HYE

332
00:22:38,898 --> 00:22:40,400
MY FAVORITE WRITER IS MARGUERITE DURAS

333
00:22:40,483 --> 00:22:42,235
I LIKE ENJOYING SOME WINE AND CHEESE
AFTER WORK

334
00:22:50,034 --> 00:22:52,328
SON JEONG-A'S CONTROVERSIAL AWARD SPEECH!

335
00:22:52,412 --> 00:22:54,747
SHE'S NOTHING WITHOUT LOVE?
CHECK OUT SON JEONG-A'S SPEECH

336
00:22:57,125 --> 00:23:00,712
I feel most alive when I'm acting
and when I'm in love.

337
00:23:00,879 --> 00:23:03,965
And I've never been ashamed
of my emotions.

338
00:23:04,841 --> 00:23:07,176
I'm nothing without love.

339
00:23:07,844 --> 00:23:12,140
My goal is to continue portraying
different kinds of love in my acting.

340
00:23:12,390 --> 00:23:13,474
Thank you.

341
00:23:19,188 --> 00:23:21,858
ACTRESS OF THE YEAR, SON JEONG-A

342
00:23:21,983 --> 00:23:23,401
Congratulations.

343
00:23:27,071 --> 00:23:28,489
I see.

344
00:23:28,573 --> 00:23:30,950
This was why it was controversial.

345
00:23:34,495 --> 00:23:35,496
My gosh!

346
00:23:35,705 --> 00:23:37,749
When did you two get here?

347
00:23:37,999 --> 00:23:40,460
Loving your junior colleagues is
also love!

348
00:23:41,252 --> 00:23:44,422
What if you end up hating her
at the end of this?

349
00:23:44,505 --> 00:23:47,926
Rumors say she only talks to men.

350
00:23:48,009 --> 00:23:49,218
- What?
- What?

351
00:23:49,844 --> 00:23:50,887
No way.

352
00:23:55,516 --> 00:23:57,310
Don't you two have work to do?

353
00:23:58,186 --> 00:24:00,313
Talking about celebrities is fun, huh?

354
00:24:00,396 --> 00:24:03,733
This was the highlight of my day.
Back to work!

355
00:24:04,817 --> 00:24:06,986
I have an update for you.

356
00:24:07,070 --> 00:24:09,322
One of the pop-up display cases is wobbly.

357
00:24:09,405 --> 00:24:11,199
Should I call HOME and ask about repairs?

358
00:24:11,282 --> 00:24:12,867
- Yeah, please do.
- Okay.

359
00:24:19,332 --> 00:24:21,793
Is it true that you use
seasonal ingredients in the soup?

360
00:24:22,877 --> 00:24:25,630
Oh, peas? Okay.

361
00:24:25,713 --> 00:24:28,257
I'll book a table for two
at 5:30 p.m. on the 2nd.

362
00:24:28,549 --> 00:24:31,094
I'd like a table in a quiet section
for us to talk, please.

363
00:24:32,095 --> 00:24:33,429
Okay, thank you.

364
00:24:36,349 --> 00:24:39,644
There's a 46% chance of rain
in the afternoon.

365
00:24:41,396 --> 00:24:43,022
I'll bring an umbrella, just in case.

366
00:24:43,106 --> 00:24:46,359
A TABLE FOR TWO AT 5:30 P.M.,
PEA SOUP, PACK AN UMBRELLA

367
00:24:47,402 --> 00:24:48,528
Check this out.

368
00:24:48,695 --> 00:24:49,946
- Hey.
- Hey.

369
00:24:50,029 --> 00:24:51,155
What's Mr. Song doing?

370
00:24:52,532 --> 00:24:54,575
No idea. Maybe he's started a new project?

371
00:24:54,909 --> 00:24:57,829
You could say he's started
the biggest project of his life.

372
00:24:57,912 --> 00:25:01,165
You guys need to go to the hotel
with a toolbox.

373
00:25:01,457 --> 00:25:03,751
- The hotel?
- One of the display cases is wobbly.

374
00:25:04,002 --> 00:25:06,295
Check on all the furniture
while you're there.

375
00:25:06,462 --> 00:25:07,505
I'll go!

376
00:25:10,383 --> 00:25:12,552
- I can do it.
- You?

377
00:25:12,635 --> 00:25:15,680
You don't need to do everything,
but thanks!

378
00:25:15,763 --> 00:25:16,848
No worries.

379
00:25:17,557 --> 00:25:18,683
See you.

380
00:25:20,018 --> 00:25:21,144
So, we don't need to go?

381
00:25:36,367 --> 00:25:38,494
- Ui-yeong.
- Tae-seop!

382
00:25:39,412 --> 00:25:41,497
You came to fix it yourself?

383
00:25:41,581 --> 00:25:43,583
Yeah, how are you?

384
00:25:43,833 --> 00:25:44,876
I'm good.

385
00:25:45,293 --> 00:25:47,837
Do you remember Ms. Son Jeong-a?

386
00:25:47,920 --> 00:25:50,590
- Yeah.
- I'm her manager at the hotel

387
00:25:50,673 --> 00:25:52,341
or something like that now.

388
00:25:52,425 --> 00:25:54,761
Really? I know you love her.

389
00:25:54,927 --> 00:25:56,679
Yeah, so I'm a little on edge.

390
00:25:57,597 --> 00:25:58,973
I've read all articles about her

391
00:25:59,057 --> 00:26:01,517
and even studied her social media pages.

392
00:26:02,602 --> 00:26:04,145
Her social media?

393
00:26:04,937 --> 00:26:06,105
Do you use them?

394
00:26:07,106 --> 00:26:08,107
Yeah.

395
00:26:10,526 --> 00:26:12,737
How do I fix this?

396
00:26:12,987 --> 00:26:15,364
It's like I'm looking through her drawers.

397
00:26:16,449 --> 00:26:18,576
She's a foodie.

398
00:26:18,659 --> 00:26:20,995
CAFE TOUR

399
00:26:23,873 --> 00:26:24,916
My gosh.

400
00:26:25,416 --> 00:26:28,002
You're surely having a lot of fun
snooping around her drawers.

401
00:26:28,836 --> 00:26:32,465
Ui-yeong is mostly in charge
of purchasing ingredients for the hotel

402
00:26:32,548 --> 00:26:36,177
so she's probably been
to all the best restaurants in Seoul.

403
00:26:36,260 --> 00:26:39,180
She won't be impressed
with just any restaurant, then.

404
00:26:40,056 --> 00:26:41,432
Should I find another place?

405
00:26:42,850 --> 00:26:44,560
Close her drawers for now.

406
00:26:44,644 --> 00:26:46,229
Look at this one first.

407
00:26:46,312 --> 00:26:47,855
It keeps dragging on the floor.

408
00:26:47,939 --> 00:26:48,940
Oh, right.

409
00:26:49,357 --> 00:26:51,526
- Can I see it?
- Yeah, I'll step aside.

410
00:26:51,609 --> 00:26:55,029
Didn't you say it was expensive marble
imported from Italy?

411
00:26:55,113 --> 00:26:57,156
Yeah, could you hold it like this?

412
00:26:57,240 --> 00:26:58,366
- Like this?
- Yeah.

413
00:27:05,414 --> 00:27:06,666
All good.

414
00:27:08,000 --> 00:27:11,045
Are you that excited about the date?

415
00:27:11,796 --> 00:27:14,090
It's our one-and-only first date.

416
00:27:14,423 --> 00:27:17,301
I'm getting more excited
now that I've planned so much.

417
00:27:17,677 --> 00:27:18,719
Gosh.

418
00:27:59,302 --> 00:28:00,678
WELCOME SON JEONG-A
WE HOPE YOU A COMFORTABLE AND JOYFUL STAY

419
00:28:06,184 --> 00:28:08,060
This should be enough.

420
00:28:08,144 --> 00:28:10,271
One more thing, though.

421
00:28:18,446 --> 00:28:21,824
I'm Lee Ui-yeong.
I'll be helping you during your stay.

422
00:28:24,160 --> 00:28:25,912
Nice to meet you. I'm Son Jeong-a.

423
00:28:27,788 --> 00:28:31,000
Please look around and let me know anytime
if you need anything.

424
00:28:35,254 --> 00:28:36,255
Oh?

425
00:28:37,673 --> 00:28:40,384
Wow, I've been reading this book.

426
00:28:41,802 --> 00:28:44,305
You love this author, right?

427
00:28:44,680 --> 00:28:46,807
I thought I'd prepare her newest book.

428
00:28:47,600 --> 00:28:49,143
But you beat me.

429
00:28:49,435 --> 00:28:51,354
I got it as soon as it was out.

430
00:28:51,437 --> 00:28:52,438
I see.

431
00:28:56,776 --> 00:28:59,362
Hotels usually prepare fresh flowers.

432
00:28:59,612 --> 00:29:01,614
Did you purposely put
a photo of them instead?

433
00:29:02,531 --> 00:29:04,450
You're allergic to flowers.

434
00:29:04,617 --> 00:29:06,410
ACTRESS OF THE YEAR, SON JEONG-A

435
00:29:13,376 --> 00:29:18,005
MAYBE ALLERGIC TO POLLEN?

436
00:29:20,049 --> 00:29:22,927
I've never told anyone that
in fear that they'd think I was picky.

437
00:29:23,552 --> 00:29:25,304
But you noticed before I told you.

438
00:29:30,268 --> 00:29:31,310
So

439
00:29:32,561 --> 00:29:34,355
what do you think about the rumor?

440
00:29:35,064 --> 00:29:36,232
Do you think it's true?

441
00:29:37,566 --> 00:29:38,609
Well...

442
00:29:38,693 --> 00:29:40,319
Among the three guys

443
00:29:40,486 --> 00:29:42,238
who do you think is my real love?

444
00:29:46,367 --> 00:29:47,368
I believe

445
00:29:48,077 --> 00:29:50,871
my role is to make your stay at our hotel

446
00:29:50,955 --> 00:29:55,334
as comfortable and relaxing as possible.

447
00:29:56,419 --> 00:29:59,880
Mr. Eun picked
such a smart person for the job.

448
00:30:01,007 --> 00:30:02,133
Nice to meet you.

449
00:30:02,341 --> 00:30:03,342
Thank you.

450
00:30:04,427 --> 00:30:07,680
Oh, and I always drink
two cups of coffee per day.

451
00:30:07,763 --> 00:30:09,974
But the coffee at the hotel is
too bitter for me

452
00:30:10,057 --> 00:30:12,310
so could you get me
some more fruity beans?

453
00:30:12,893 --> 00:30:15,146
I'll prepare
some light-medium roast beans.

454
00:30:16,147 --> 00:30:18,816
I'll probably also need a few more pajamas

455
00:30:18,899 --> 00:30:20,276
and an extra humidifier, please.

456
00:30:20,359 --> 00:30:21,569
Okay, noted.

457
00:30:25,281 --> 00:30:26,657
PREPARE A DRIP COFFEE SET
AND LIGHT-MEDIUM ROAST BEANS

458
00:30:26,741 --> 00:30:29,452
Next, a drip set
and light-medium roast beans.

459
00:30:30,870 --> 00:30:32,371
Oh, no, I'd better get going.

460
00:30:39,879 --> 00:30:41,380
We're closing soon.

461
00:30:42,631 --> 00:30:44,383
- Hey.
- What?

462
00:30:58,522 --> 00:31:01,275
You're just a small stage director.
Whiskey isn't your thing.

463
00:31:01,484 --> 00:31:02,777
Are you here to say something?

464
00:31:03,486 --> 00:31:04,737
You saw right through me.

465
00:31:06,655 --> 00:31:08,532
You know the performance this weekend?

466
00:31:09,617 --> 00:31:13,704
Yeah, it's for Seungbo Group,
the theater's sponsor company, right?

467
00:31:14,705 --> 00:31:16,123
I need you to perform.

468
00:31:17,375 --> 00:31:21,545
Se-hyeon had to go to his hometown
becauase his mother is ill.

469
00:31:21,796 --> 00:31:23,005
What happened to her?

470
00:31:23,881 --> 00:31:25,591
She's just really ill.

471
00:31:29,261 --> 00:31:30,763
See you at the rehearsal tomorrow.

472
00:31:31,597 --> 00:31:33,140
- You're leaving already?
- Yeah.

473
00:31:33,474 --> 00:31:35,017
The whiskey tastes too fancy.

474
00:31:38,187 --> 00:31:39,772
Okay, see you.

475
00:31:45,486 --> 00:31:47,279
We're really closed... Oh?

476
00:31:47,363 --> 00:31:49,657
Can I get some drip coffee?
With fruity beans?

477
00:31:50,241 --> 00:31:51,575
Sure, come in.

478
00:31:58,416 --> 00:32:01,001
- Were you working until now?
- Yeah, I had a lot to do.

479
00:32:04,296 --> 00:32:05,673
Aren't you a bit hungry?

480
00:32:10,678 --> 00:32:13,597
Mom, I'm grabbing a bite
after working until late.

481
00:32:15,933 --> 00:32:18,769
- Here.
- I can't drink for a while.

482
00:32:19,645 --> 00:32:20,729
Why not?

483
00:32:20,896 --> 00:32:22,565
I have work tomorrow

484
00:32:22,648 --> 00:32:24,400
and my mom's been unhappy with me.

485
00:32:31,240 --> 00:32:33,784
By the way, are we allowed to eat here?

486
00:32:33,868 --> 00:32:35,828
Of course. Should we play some music?

487
00:32:36,078 --> 00:32:37,329
Sure, sounds good.

488
00:32:38,664 --> 00:32:40,708
It's nice to have a friend
who works at a cafe.

489
00:33:02,229 --> 00:33:03,230
Hey

490
00:33:03,564 --> 00:33:06,942
this is one of the three meals
I've promised you, okay?

491
00:33:08,319 --> 00:33:10,196
I can't believe you're keeping a tally.

492
00:33:10,279 --> 00:33:12,948
This is nothing compared
to what I've done for you.

493
00:33:13,282 --> 00:33:16,160
No, you're clearly enjoying it.
You got some sauce there.

494
00:33:18,078 --> 00:33:20,748
And you were the one who volunteered.

495
00:33:20,831 --> 00:33:24,126
You can't tell me to pay you back
when you volunteeered.

496
00:33:25,628 --> 00:33:26,795
I guess so.

497
00:33:27,421 --> 00:33:28,756
You're right.

498
00:33:30,007 --> 00:33:31,550
You got some on your face, too.

499
00:33:35,471 --> 00:33:37,973
I'm not the type to be
all up in anyone's business

500
00:33:39,016 --> 00:33:40,851
but I can't stop being nosy around you.

501
00:33:43,729 --> 00:33:44,730
See?

502
00:33:53,030 --> 00:33:57,159
Don't do that to people.
That could lead them on.

503
00:33:57,660 --> 00:33:59,370
You're always so weirdly close.

504
00:34:01,455 --> 00:34:03,040
I wouldn't exactly say

505
00:34:05,000 --> 00:34:06,585
you're getting the wrong idea.

506
00:34:09,129 --> 00:34:10,130
Huh?

507
00:34:12,341 --> 00:34:15,469
You seem to think I don't mean anything

508
00:34:15,844 --> 00:34:17,721
but we went on a blind date

509
00:34:18,472 --> 00:34:20,432
even though I was filling in
for someone else.

510
00:34:20,766 --> 00:34:22,309
And we're becoming closer.

511
00:34:23,519 --> 00:34:26,522
I've been having fun since the first day.

512
00:34:27,481 --> 00:34:28,816
Don't you feel the same?

513
00:34:32,069 --> 00:34:33,070
Hmm?

514
00:34:35,489 --> 00:34:36,782
It's nothing serious.

515
00:34:37,950 --> 00:34:38,993
You know

516
00:34:39,577 --> 00:34:42,037
you make my life interesting these days.

517
00:34:43,455 --> 00:34:44,456
Just keep eating.

518
00:34:44,540 --> 00:34:47,001
Eat first, and take your time
to digest it all.

519
00:35:00,639 --> 00:35:01,807
How are you getting home?

520
00:35:02,141 --> 00:35:04,018
I called a cab. It should be here soon.

521
00:35:05,102 --> 00:35:07,313
I have to go to my rehearsal now.

522
00:35:09,356 --> 00:35:11,150
- Get home safely.
- Okay.

523
00:35:11,275 --> 00:35:12,735
Let's grab another meal sometime.

524
00:35:12,818 --> 00:35:14,194
Sure, bye.

525
00:35:20,367 --> 00:35:21,410
See you.

526
00:35:41,013 --> 00:35:42,431
What was that about?

527
00:35:43,891 --> 00:35:47,186
Does he like me,
or do I just make his life interesting?

528
00:35:49,938 --> 00:35:52,358
SONG TAE-SEOP HAS REPLIED TO YOUR STORY

529
00:35:52,441 --> 00:35:53,859
GOOD WORK TODAY.
I CAN'T WAIT FOR SATURDAY. GOODNIGHT

530
00:35:53,942 --> 00:35:55,277
Good work today.

531
00:35:55,361 --> 00:35:57,112
I can't wait for Saturday.

532
00:35:57,613 --> 00:35:58,656
Goodnight.

533
00:36:02,326 --> 00:36:03,869
LEE UI-YEONG

534
00:36:04,161 --> 00:36:06,955
Thanks, goodnight to you, too.

535
00:36:07,039 --> 00:36:08,207
See you soon!

536
00:36:17,132 --> 00:36:18,384
- Come in.
- Okay.

537
00:36:18,759 --> 00:36:20,260
- I'm just on the phone.
- Okay.

538
00:36:20,886 --> 00:36:21,887
Hey.

539
00:36:22,471 --> 00:36:23,555
What about the casting?

540
00:36:25,474 --> 00:36:27,559
Why would you do something
I didn't even ask for?

541
00:36:27,643 --> 00:36:30,354
The performance is just for the employees.

542
00:36:30,562 --> 00:36:33,899
I'm the wife of the CEO.
Can't you be more supportive?

543
00:36:33,982 --> 00:36:35,859
Whatever. I can't go.

544
00:36:36,360 --> 00:36:37,861
Dr. Shin's coming tomorrow.

545
00:36:38,696 --> 00:36:40,614
I need to have a long talk with him.

546
00:36:41,824 --> 00:36:44,410
It's already giving me a headache.
Just send me the address.

547
00:36:44,493 --> 00:36:46,161
Okay, will do.

548
00:36:50,374 --> 00:36:53,752
I just have a favor to ask you.

549
00:36:53,836 --> 00:36:55,045
Sure, what is it?

550
00:36:55,129 --> 00:36:58,799
Could you bring a bouquet
to an address I give you tomorrow?

551
00:36:58,882 --> 00:37:01,635
It's an important show, but I can't go.

552
00:37:03,762 --> 00:37:04,847
And...

553
00:37:05,973 --> 00:37:07,850
- this is the card for the bouquet.
- Okay.

554
00:37:07,933 --> 00:37:10,644
No need to watch the show.
Just deliver the bouquet for me.

555
00:37:10,811 --> 00:37:11,895
Okay, then.

556
00:37:11,979 --> 00:37:16,358
And I'd like to invite a friend here
for dinner tomorrow.

557
00:37:16,442 --> 00:37:17,776
How many of them?

558
00:37:17,860 --> 00:37:18,861
Just one.

559
00:37:19,236 --> 00:37:21,363
He'll arrive at the hotel around 7 p.m.

560
00:37:21,447 --> 00:37:26,076
Could you prepare something Western
that goes with wine?

561
00:37:26,160 --> 00:37:29,329
Sure, we'll prepare the dinner
as soon as your guest arrives.

562
00:37:29,413 --> 00:37:30,831
He'll also be sleeping over.

563
00:37:30,914 --> 00:37:32,833
Please make sure
the security is extra strong.

564
00:37:32,916 --> 00:37:34,209
Okay, will do.

565
00:37:40,007 --> 00:37:41,675
Should we have gotten two?

566
00:37:42,009 --> 00:37:43,135
Will this be enough?

567
00:37:43,218 --> 00:37:46,346
Your uncle isn't that greedy with food.
Or anything, for that matter.

568
00:37:50,017 --> 00:37:52,186
Are you sure he's not greedy?

569
00:37:54,480 --> 00:37:55,731
Is this the wrong house?

570
00:37:59,067 --> 00:38:00,277
Wet wipes.

571
00:38:01,862 --> 00:38:03,280
Hydrogen peroxide.

572
00:38:03,405 --> 00:38:05,240
Band-aids. Are you going to a boot camp?

573
00:38:06,241 --> 00:38:07,242
Blanket.

574
00:38:07,326 --> 00:38:09,495
Are you sure you're going on a date?

575
00:38:09,912 --> 00:38:12,706
I don't know what might happen
on the date.

576
00:38:12,790 --> 00:38:14,958
And they're all useful to have, anyway.

577
00:38:16,543 --> 00:38:18,921
Sua, go wash your hands.
Let's eat the pizza.

578
00:38:19,004 --> 00:38:20,088
Okay.

579
00:38:26,720 --> 00:38:29,556
I've never seen a guy prepare so much
for a date.

580
00:38:29,640 --> 00:38:31,266
Are you nervous or just crazy?

581
00:38:31,767 --> 00:38:32,851
I'm just excited.

582
00:38:33,936 --> 00:38:36,647
Dad! Look at this!

583
00:38:39,233 --> 00:38:40,275
A timetable?

584
00:38:40,359 --> 00:38:41,652
PICK UP EUI-YEONG AT 5 P.M.

585
00:38:41,735 --> 00:38:43,070
DINNER FROM 5:30 TO 7 P.M.
COFFEE FROM 7 TO 7:30 P.M.

586
00:38:44,530 --> 00:38:45,906
This isn't a dream, is it?

587
00:38:46,281 --> 00:38:49,076
I thought guys like him
only existed in dreams.

588
00:38:50,911 --> 00:38:54,164
Sua, can you help me pick out my outfit
after we eat?

589
00:38:55,249 --> 00:38:56,291
Sure.

590
00:38:57,042 --> 00:38:59,169
Sua, I'm better than him, right?

591
00:38:59,253 --> 00:39:01,755
Not a chance. He's a million times better.

592
00:39:01,839 --> 00:39:03,674
Hey, that hurts!

593
00:39:03,757 --> 00:39:05,884
Sorry, I thought it was a dream.
Keep eating.

594
00:39:05,968 --> 00:39:08,262
DEUKGEUN DEUKGEUN GYM

595
00:39:23,610 --> 00:39:26,029
DEUKGEUN DEUKGEUN GYM

596
00:39:28,156 --> 00:39:30,409
Isn't it so hot today?

597
00:39:31,326 --> 00:39:35,163
That just proves
we worked really hard today.

598
00:39:35,706 --> 00:39:38,584
No, I think
the air conditioners are broken.

599
00:39:39,585 --> 00:39:42,254
What are you talking about?
We just fixed them.

600
00:39:44,464 --> 00:39:47,009
What? They're really not working.

601
00:39:47,092 --> 00:39:48,677
See?

602
00:40:03,233 --> 00:40:05,611
It would've been cheaper
to get new ones at this point!

603
00:40:11,491 --> 00:40:12,784
Hello?

604
00:40:13,410 --> 00:40:15,162
Hi, Hyun-min.

605
00:40:15,245 --> 00:40:18,790
Seung-jun! I'm off early today.
We can meet earlier.

606
00:40:19,499 --> 00:40:24,171
But my gym's air conditioners are broken.
I need to fix them...

607
00:40:24,504 --> 00:40:26,548
I don't think I can leave the gym.

608
00:40:27,090 --> 00:40:28,091
Oh, no.

609
00:40:28,175 --> 00:40:30,552
Isn't it too hot in there
without air conditioning?

610
00:40:30,636 --> 00:40:32,638
Yeah, it feels like a sauna.

611
00:40:33,138 --> 00:40:35,140
Gosh, I can't even breathe.

612
00:40:35,432 --> 00:40:39,269
Let me fix this and get back to you.

613
00:40:39,561 --> 00:40:40,604
- Okay.
- I'm so sorry.

614
00:40:40,687 --> 00:40:41,772
It's okay.

615
00:40:47,819 --> 00:40:51,657
DEUKGEUN DEUKGEUN GYM

616
00:40:52,240 --> 00:40:54,159
It's too hot, right? I'm so sorry.

617
00:40:54,242 --> 00:40:56,370
Sorry. Here's a fresh towel.

618
00:40:56,453 --> 00:40:58,038
Sorry, it's too hot, isn't it?

619
00:40:58,121 --> 00:40:59,289
- I know it's hot.
- Here's a towel.

620
00:40:59,373 --> 00:41:00,415
Here's a towel.

621
00:41:02,084 --> 00:41:04,002
It feels like a boot camp here.

622
00:41:04,086 --> 00:41:05,796
Even my underwear is drenched.

623
00:41:05,879 --> 00:41:07,089
Sorry.

624
00:41:07,172 --> 00:41:08,799
Don't push yourself too hard.

625
00:41:08,882 --> 00:41:10,884
I'll give you an extention on your pass.
Sorry.

626
00:41:30,862 --> 00:41:32,406
Let's cool down.

627
00:41:32,781 --> 00:41:33,824
Hyun-min!

628
00:41:38,245 --> 00:41:40,789
- It's hot, right? Here.
- Thank you.

629
00:41:41,456 --> 00:41:43,583
Which one would you like?

630
00:41:43,750 --> 00:41:44,751
Thank you.

631
00:41:45,794 --> 00:41:46,795
Wait.

632
00:41:47,254 --> 00:41:49,673
You look familiar.

633
00:41:49,756 --> 00:41:51,466
Don't we know each other from somewhere?

634
00:41:52,676 --> 00:41:54,344
- Well...
- Don’t worry about your membership.

635
00:41:55,262 --> 00:41:56,555
I'm not sure.

636
00:41:57,222 --> 00:41:59,016
That's a bit much.

637
00:41:59,433 --> 00:42:01,852
- No, that's not it.
- Seriously.

638
00:42:01,935 --> 00:42:03,478
It's a lot of sweat.

639
00:42:03,562 --> 00:42:07,899
Let me give you an extra towel.

640
00:42:07,983 --> 00:42:08,984
Thanks.

641
00:42:13,280 --> 00:42:14,322
I'm out!

642
00:42:14,406 --> 00:42:15,699
Okay, see you.

643
00:42:16,366 --> 00:42:18,702
CLOSED OVER THE WEEKEND
TO FIX THE AIR CONDITIONERS

644
00:42:18,785 --> 00:42:21,079
Seung-jun! Take a break.

645
00:42:21,329 --> 00:42:22,330
Sure.

646
00:42:23,248 --> 00:42:24,624
He's so hard-working.

647
00:42:27,169 --> 00:42:28,170
Here.

648
00:42:33,842 --> 00:42:35,260
Thanks for today.

649
00:42:35,761 --> 00:42:37,304
How did you know to come here?

650
00:42:38,180 --> 00:42:41,600
It's written right on your shirt.
"Deukgeun Deukgeun."

651
00:42:42,642 --> 00:42:44,686
I can still remember you
taking that shirt off.

652
00:42:44,770 --> 00:42:46,438
You're a sicko.

653
00:42:47,189 --> 00:42:48,523
But you like them.

654
00:42:56,990 --> 00:42:58,700
Is that strawberry-flavored?

655
00:42:59,284 --> 00:43:00,285
Let me have a bite.

656
00:43:27,354 --> 00:43:29,856
It's still a date...

657
00:43:31,483 --> 00:43:32,609
Something bright.

658
00:43:33,110 --> 00:43:34,152
Let's see.

659
00:43:36,279 --> 00:43:39,449
No, if I dress up too much

660
00:43:40,492 --> 00:43:41,743
I'll look like a rookie.

661
00:43:47,124 --> 00:43:49,209
How about this one? Or this?

662
00:43:50,627 --> 00:43:51,711
Or jeans?

663
00:44:00,762 --> 00:44:01,805
Alright.

664
00:44:12,941 --> 00:44:14,276
Perfect.

665
00:44:14,359 --> 00:44:16,820
This looks casual but nice.

666
00:44:17,612 --> 00:44:22,117
MEORU ART CENTER

667
00:44:24,077 --> 00:44:25,245
Thank you.

668
00:44:31,293 --> 00:44:33,420
- Enjoy the show.
- Thank you.

669
00:44:33,503 --> 00:44:34,629
- Here.
- Hello.

670
00:44:34,713 --> 00:44:36,381
- Enjoy the show.
- Thank you.

671
00:44:36,464 --> 00:44:39,134
- Hello.
- Could you deliver these to someone?

672
00:44:39,217 --> 00:44:42,804
Of course, you can leave it with me,
and I'll give it to the person.

673
00:44:42,888 --> 00:44:44,139
Who is it for?

674
00:44:44,222 --> 00:44:46,433
Oh, give me a sec.

675
00:44:49,352 --> 00:44:51,354
DEAR JI-SU,
CONGRATULATIONS ON YOUR SHOW

676
00:44:52,147 --> 00:44:53,398
Ji-su?

677
00:44:53,481 --> 00:44:55,317
Oh, you mean Mr. Shin Ji-su?

678
00:44:56,359 --> 00:44:57,360
Oh...

679
00:44:57,861 --> 00:44:59,196
Yeah, Mr. Shin Ji-su.

680
00:44:59,279 --> 00:45:00,697
Okay.

681
00:45:04,618 --> 00:45:06,620
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

682
00:45:07,495 --> 00:45:09,706
Hello, may I see your tickets?

683
00:45:10,957 --> 00:45:12,751
- Enjoy the show.
- Thank you.

684
00:45:12,834 --> 00:45:13,835
Thank you.

685
00:45:17,631 --> 00:45:19,299
THE SEAGULL

686
00:45:20,717 --> 00:45:22,093
THE SEAGULL

687
00:45:22,469 --> 00:45:26,431
So, he knows Jeong-a?

688
00:45:27,557 --> 00:45:28,683
Is it...

689
00:45:34,731 --> 00:45:35,982
MS. S, THE QUEEN OF ROMANCE,
IS THE QUEEN OF SCANDALS?

690
00:45:36,066 --> 00:45:38,068
THE QUEEN'S MANY MEN...

691
00:45:39,236 --> 00:45:43,073
"She's in a common-law relationship
with Dr. A, a surgeon who had a wife

692
00:45:43,156 --> 00:45:45,617
but has an affair with Mr. B,
a director, at a hotel

693
00:45:45,700 --> 00:45:47,410
while being a sugar mommy to a model."

694
00:45:49,120 --> 00:45:51,706
THE SCANDAL IS ONLY GROWING
WITH HER COMPLICATED DATING LIFE

695
00:46:19,109 --> 00:46:20,193
Hey, Ui-yeong.

696
00:46:21,319 --> 00:46:22,779
Your hairstyle's changed.

697
00:46:23,446 --> 00:46:24,739
And where are your glasses?

698
00:46:25,156 --> 00:46:26,574
I thought I'd dress up a bit.

699
00:46:26,658 --> 00:46:28,285
It's our first date, after all.

700
00:46:30,203 --> 00:46:32,664
I should've dressed up more, too.

701
00:46:33,081 --> 00:46:35,583
You look as beautiful as always.

702
00:46:35,917 --> 00:46:37,585
"As always"?

703
00:46:40,505 --> 00:46:41,715
Ready for dinner?

704
00:46:41,798 --> 00:46:44,050
I found a restaurant nearby.

705
00:46:44,134 --> 00:46:47,095
A one-star Michelin chef
recently opened it.

706
00:46:47,637 --> 00:46:48,930
It's closed.

707
00:46:52,225 --> 00:46:53,476
UNFORTUNATELY, WE HAD TO CLOSE
DUE TO A DEATH IN THE CHEF'S FAMILY

708
00:46:53,560 --> 00:46:55,395
Oh, they're closed...

709
00:47:00,400 --> 00:47:03,153
I also prepared an alternative,
just in case.

710
00:47:03,236 --> 00:47:04,863
It's a five-minute walk.

711
00:47:04,946 --> 00:47:07,365
I didn't book a table,
but it's still early

712
00:47:07,449 --> 00:47:08,867
so I'm sure we can get a seat.

713
00:47:11,202 --> 00:47:12,829
Ms. Lee Ui-jin?

714
00:47:13,038 --> 00:47:14,456
- Is Ms. Lee Ui-jin here?
- Here!

715
00:47:14,622 --> 00:47:15,749
You can come in.

716
00:47:23,798 --> 00:47:26,259
We're going to be late for the movie

717
00:47:26,551 --> 00:47:28,511
if we wait for a table here.

718
00:47:28,762 --> 00:47:30,430
Oh, then...

719
00:47:31,097 --> 00:47:32,140
Well...

720
00:47:33,558 --> 00:47:34,684
Tae-seop

721
00:47:35,435 --> 00:47:37,228
I know it's not a romantic place

722
00:47:37,312 --> 00:47:40,023
but I have a favorite restaurant nearby.

723
00:47:40,315 --> 00:47:41,858
You want to go there with me?

724
00:47:42,233 --> 00:47:43,943
That sounds good.

725
00:47:44,027 --> 00:47:45,028
Okay.

726
00:48:05,548 --> 00:48:08,176
- The table's a bit wobbly, right?
- Yeah.

727
00:48:08,259 --> 00:48:10,303
Be careful, it's hot.

728
00:48:10,387 --> 00:48:11,429
Thank you.

729
00:48:11,513 --> 00:48:12,889
- Careful.
- Thank you.

730
00:48:12,972 --> 00:48:15,225
You can move tables if it bothers you.

731
00:48:15,308 --> 00:48:16,559
No, it's fine.

732
00:48:20,605 --> 00:48:23,024
I can't believe I'm here with you.

733
00:48:23,108 --> 00:48:26,736
I'm only ever here with my colleagues
because there's a client nearby.

734
00:48:26,945 --> 00:48:28,071
I see.

735
00:48:29,406 --> 00:48:30,407
This looks great.

736
00:48:30,824 --> 00:48:31,950
Let's eat.

737
00:48:33,410 --> 00:48:34,411
Huh?

738
00:48:34,494 --> 00:48:37,539
Oh, this stops me from burning my tongue

739
00:48:37,622 --> 00:48:38,915
and lets me eat faster.

740
00:48:38,998 --> 00:48:39,999
I see.

741
00:48:42,669 --> 00:48:43,711
Like this.

742
00:48:45,797 --> 00:48:46,798
Watch out.

743
00:48:47,340 --> 00:48:48,383
Thank you.

744
00:48:49,092 --> 00:48:51,010
Go on. Try it.

745
00:48:58,184 --> 00:48:59,561
- It's amazing.
- Right?

746
00:48:59,644 --> 00:49:00,770
I'm glad you like it.

747
00:49:04,774 --> 00:49:05,984
It's so good.

748
00:49:08,486 --> 00:49:09,487
Thank you.

749
00:49:10,321 --> 00:49:12,073
Oh, hold on a sec.

750
00:49:48,818 --> 00:49:49,819
Great.

751
00:49:49,986 --> 00:49:51,112
- All good.
- All good.

752
00:49:55,408 --> 00:49:56,910
You're pretty good at that.

753
00:49:56,993 --> 00:49:58,411
It's nothing.

754
00:49:58,495 --> 00:49:59,954
No, it was impressive.

755
00:50:01,164 --> 00:50:04,167
How did you start designing furniture?

756
00:50:06,252 --> 00:50:08,463
My family didn't have a dining table
for some time

757
00:50:08,546 --> 00:50:10,173
because we suddenly became poor.

758
00:50:10,924 --> 00:50:13,593
But it wasn't just the table
that was taken from us.

759
00:50:14,427 --> 00:50:16,429
We stopped eating together

760
00:50:16,971 --> 00:50:19,891
or talking to each other.
We became distant from each other.

761
00:50:20,725 --> 00:50:23,436
That was when I realized
furniture wasn't just an object.

762
00:50:23,770 --> 00:50:26,773
It was from that point on
that I realized it was so important.

763
00:50:27,440 --> 00:50:30,401
And I wanted to do something important
because I was in my twenties.

764
00:50:30,985 --> 00:50:32,070
I see.

765
00:50:32,737 --> 00:50:34,948
I worked nonstop
since starting my business.

766
00:50:36,449 --> 00:50:38,326
How were you in your twenties?

767
00:50:38,493 --> 00:50:40,370
You're so bubbly.
You must've been so social.

768
00:50:40,537 --> 00:50:42,288
No, I only had a handful.

769
00:50:42,830 --> 00:50:45,166
I wasn't well-off
in my younger years, either

770
00:50:45,250 --> 00:50:47,126
so I only ever thought about myself.

771
00:50:47,210 --> 00:50:50,922
I thought everyone should live a hard life
because I was living one.

772
00:50:51,256 --> 00:50:53,341
I didn't know you ever had a hard time.

773
00:50:54,050 --> 00:50:55,802
I don't have all that many fond memories.

774
00:50:56,177 --> 00:50:57,929
I never went on any trips

775
00:50:58,012 --> 00:51:00,515
and rejected every guy,
saying I didn't have time to date.

776
00:51:00,598 --> 00:51:02,684
I see. That's okay.

777
00:51:02,767 --> 00:51:05,353
You can enjoy all of that now.

778
00:51:08,106 --> 00:51:09,148
That's right.

779
00:51:09,649 --> 00:51:12,193
That's why I like how things are now.

780
00:51:13,194 --> 00:51:15,697
I'm glad we met now.

781
00:51:45,810 --> 00:51:48,896
Humans are funny.

782
00:51:51,649 --> 00:51:56,112
But I want to trust him one more time.

783
00:51:59,741 --> 00:52:00,825
Why are you crying?

784
00:52:01,743 --> 00:52:02,827
Are you that sad?

785
00:52:02,910 --> 00:52:05,872
No, it's my eyes.

786
00:52:06,164 --> 00:52:07,290
Do they hurt?

787
00:52:08,333 --> 00:52:10,001
Let's get out.

788
00:52:13,630 --> 00:52:15,256
Even after having been betrayed once

789
00:52:16,466 --> 00:52:19,677
I can't help but give him another chance.

790
00:52:23,139 --> 00:52:25,558
- Are you alright?
- Yeah.

791
00:52:25,892 --> 00:52:27,894
I'm not used to wearing contact lenses.

792
00:52:27,977 --> 00:52:29,937
I think something got in my eye.
It stings.

793
00:52:30,521 --> 00:52:32,023
It looks pretty serious.

794
00:52:32,106 --> 00:52:33,900
It's really red. Look at me.

795
00:52:34,359 --> 00:52:35,610
What? No...

796
00:52:36,402 --> 00:52:38,196
Let me look.

797
00:52:45,078 --> 00:52:47,872
This won't do. Take your lenses out first.

798
00:52:58,007 --> 00:52:59,217
Are you better?

799
00:52:59,300 --> 00:53:00,760
Did you take them out? How is it?

800
00:53:00,843 --> 00:53:02,095
Much better.

801
00:53:02,178 --> 00:53:03,930
Should we head back in?

802
00:53:04,430 --> 00:53:05,556
Where?

803
00:53:06,057 --> 00:53:08,017
You can't even see anything.

804
00:53:08,101 --> 00:53:10,687
Let's watch it another time.
You should go home.

805
00:53:10,770 --> 00:53:12,522
No, I can't.

806
00:53:12,605 --> 00:53:14,148
We have to watch the movie today.

807
00:53:14,232 --> 00:53:16,609
But you can't even see properly.

808
00:53:18,069 --> 00:53:19,112
Then...

809
00:53:19,195 --> 00:53:22,240
Oh, do you want to watch it at my house?

810
00:53:23,074 --> 00:53:24,617
Your house?

811
00:53:24,701 --> 00:53:27,745
No, I don't mean it like that.

812
00:53:28,037 --> 00:53:29,914
I just don't want to say
"Next time" again.

813
00:53:31,082 --> 00:53:32,125
Oh.

814
00:53:33,710 --> 00:53:35,503
Should we get some popcorn, too?

815
00:53:37,088 --> 00:53:38,131
Yeah.

816
00:53:39,006 --> 00:53:40,049
Oh.

817
00:53:41,300 --> 00:53:43,219
Hold my arm and follow me.

818
00:53:56,107 --> 00:53:58,317
Okay.

819
00:53:58,943 --> 00:54:00,528
The chauffeur should be here soon.

820
00:54:01,362 --> 00:54:05,032
Sorry. I have a license,
but I've never driven a car.

821
00:54:05,867 --> 00:54:06,868
It's okay.

822
00:54:08,369 --> 00:54:09,370
Oh?

823
00:54:10,037 --> 00:54:11,664
I love this song.

824
00:54:13,207 --> 00:54:14,959
- Same.
- Really?

825
00:55:11,390 --> 00:55:13,267
Bravo!

826
00:55:13,351 --> 00:55:14,644
You were amazing!

827
00:55:17,480 --> 00:55:18,815
- Good work today.
- You too.

828
00:55:18,898 --> 00:55:20,608
- Good work.
- You too.

829
00:55:20,691 --> 00:55:21,984
- Good job.
- Good work!

830
00:55:22,068 --> 00:55:24,320
- Congrats!
- Good job.

831
00:55:24,403 --> 00:55:26,864
Ji-su, this is for you.

832
00:55:26,948 --> 00:55:28,449
Don't forget it.

833
00:55:28,533 --> 00:55:29,534
Okay.

834
00:55:37,875 --> 00:55:39,168
Congratulations on your show.

835
00:55:39,252 --> 00:55:40,920
I have big news for you.

836
00:55:41,003 --> 00:55:42,505
Please meet me at The Hills.

837
00:55:45,466 --> 00:55:47,426
MEORU ART CENTER

838
00:55:47,510 --> 00:55:48,636
Mr. Shin.

839
00:55:49,095 --> 00:55:50,888
I'm Kim Ji-yeong, a reporter for Daily N.

840
00:55:50,972 --> 00:55:54,433
You're the model mentioned
in the rumor about Ms. Son, right?

841
00:55:54,725 --> 00:55:56,769
How do you know Ms. Son?

842
00:55:56,978 --> 00:56:00,147
I have nothing to do with her.
Please never approach me again.

843
00:56:01,107 --> 00:56:04,402
We've confirmed that the biggest sponsor
for the theater is Seungbo Group.

844
00:56:04,485 --> 00:56:06,529
The wife of the Group's CEO is

845
00:56:06,612 --> 00:56:09,448
Ms. Son's best friend. Did you know that?

846
00:56:09,532 --> 00:56:11,367
I hear she's far more than an advisor

847
00:56:11,450 --> 00:56:14,078
when it comes to investing in the arts.

848
00:56:14,579 --> 00:56:15,580
What?

849
00:56:16,622 --> 00:56:17,874
I'm just wondering

850
00:56:18,249 --> 00:56:20,877
if you maybe made a deal with her

851
00:56:20,960 --> 00:56:23,754
in exchange for this sponsorship.

852
00:56:26,549 --> 00:56:28,634
That was so awesome.

853
00:56:28,718 --> 00:56:29,802
Hey!

854
00:56:30,428 --> 00:56:31,846
Ji-su! What are you doing?

855
00:56:31,929 --> 00:56:33,264
- You bastard!
- Are you crazy?

856
00:56:34,265 --> 00:56:35,850
You asked me get on stage on purpose.

857
00:56:35,933 --> 00:56:37,685
Yeah, how else?

858
00:56:37,768 --> 00:56:39,270
You know that's not what I mean.

859
00:56:39,353 --> 00:56:42,523
You've been paying me
with the money you get from Jeong-a!

860
00:56:43,733 --> 00:56:45,192
How could you insult me like this?

861
00:56:45,276 --> 00:56:47,737
The CEO's wife is sponsoring us
because she loves our show.

862
00:56:47,820 --> 00:56:50,907
Yeah? Why would they invest in a show
that doesn't turn a profit?

863
00:56:52,533 --> 00:56:54,744
And the wife's never even come
to watch our show.

864
00:56:55,620 --> 00:56:58,873
Stop acting
like an arrogant and childish bastard.

865
00:56:59,081 --> 00:57:00,249
It's not about paying you.

866
00:57:00,333 --> 00:57:02,752
It's about paying the rent, the cast

867
00:57:02,835 --> 00:57:04,629
for the stage outfits, food, and props!

868
00:57:04,712 --> 00:57:06,130
We've dedicated our lives to this

869
00:57:06,213 --> 00:57:07,798
and we'll do anything to perform.

870
00:57:07,882 --> 00:57:09,550
This underground shelter you seek is

871
00:57:09,634 --> 00:57:11,677
the most desperate stage for us!

872
00:57:12,011 --> 00:57:15,306
If you're going to be this uncommitted,
just quit.

873
00:57:34,951 --> 00:57:36,077
Fine, I will.

874
00:57:36,160 --> 00:57:37,662
Come on, don't be like that.

875
00:57:40,998 --> 00:57:42,041
I quit.

876
00:57:44,669 --> 00:57:46,462
He can't really quit like that!

877
00:58:05,231 --> 00:58:06,774
I'm heading to the hotel right now.

878
00:58:15,366 --> 00:58:17,618
Let me just get my glasses.

879
00:58:17,910 --> 00:58:19,537
Make yourself at home on the couch.

880
00:58:20,162 --> 00:58:21,163
Okay.

881
00:58:36,345 --> 00:58:38,055
It's sparkling clean.

882
00:58:56,615 --> 00:59:00,244
TIMETABLE

883
00:59:01,704 --> 00:59:03,456
PICK UP EUI-YEONG AT 5 P.M.

884
00:59:03,539 --> 00:59:05,041
DINNER FROM 5:30 TO 7 P.M.
COFFEE FROM 7 TO 7:30 P.M.

885
00:59:05,124 --> 00:59:06,459
MOVIE FOR 90 MINUTES

886
00:59:09,587 --> 00:59:10,588
Oh!

887
00:59:13,466 --> 00:59:16,385
You planned out the whole night?

888
00:59:17,887 --> 00:59:18,929
But...

889
00:59:19,680 --> 00:59:21,974
nothing went as planned.

890
00:59:22,058 --> 00:59:23,309
No.

891
00:59:27,646 --> 00:59:28,689
But

892
00:59:29,356 --> 00:59:30,775
I still had fun.

893
00:59:42,244 --> 00:59:44,038
Feel free to look around if you're bored.

894
00:59:44,121 --> 00:59:45,873
Oh, sure.

895
01:00:16,529 --> 01:00:17,696
Wait.

896
01:00:21,408 --> 01:00:22,493
Do you want a drink?

897
01:00:23,410 --> 01:00:26,497
I have water, sparkling water,
cola, and green tea. What would you like?

898
01:00:27,331 --> 01:00:29,792
I'll have some cold water, please.

899
01:00:31,585 --> 01:00:32,711
Wake up.

900
01:00:53,440 --> 01:00:55,484
What kind of movies do you like?

901
01:00:56,652 --> 01:01:00,406
Anything but horror, really.

902
01:01:00,990 --> 01:01:03,325
Are you scared of horror movies?

903
01:01:04,410 --> 01:01:07,872
They're so bad for my heart.

904
01:01:09,081 --> 01:01:11,458
Are you okay with horror movies?

905
01:01:11,959 --> 01:01:13,085
I can watch them.

906
01:01:13,169 --> 01:01:16,380
When I was younger,
my dad said ghosts weren't scary.

907
01:01:16,463 --> 01:01:19,258
He said people were scarier.

908
01:01:19,717 --> 01:01:21,343
I haven't been scared of ghosts since.

909
01:01:23,429 --> 01:01:25,139
That's a great comment.

910
01:01:29,810 --> 01:01:32,438
I hear that one is good.

911
01:01:35,357 --> 01:01:36,901
- This?
- Yeah.

912
01:01:39,111 --> 01:01:40,112
Should I...

913
01:01:40,905 --> 01:01:42,364
turn off the lights?

914
01:01:43,782 --> 01:01:45,117
Oh, right.

915
01:01:46,327 --> 01:01:47,369
Sure.

916
01:01:53,250 --> 01:01:56,462
This will dry out your hands.
Moisturize them often.

917
01:01:59,256 --> 01:02:01,175
You have to keep them soft.

918
01:02:06,639 --> 01:02:09,516
That's really nice.

919
01:02:57,523 --> 01:02:58,565
Hey...

920
01:02:59,775 --> 01:03:00,901
Ui-yeong.

921
01:03:02,569 --> 01:03:03,612
Yeah?

922
01:03:03,862 --> 01:03:05,781
I have something to tell you.

923
01:03:38,355 --> 01:03:39,773
- Hey.
- Mom!

924
01:03:44,445 --> 01:03:45,571
Oh, my.

925
01:03:46,655 --> 01:03:49,158
Are you okay? Are you hurt?

926
01:03:49,241 --> 01:03:51,660
Oh, gosh! What do I do?

927
01:03:51,869 --> 01:03:53,537
I'm so sorry!

928
01:03:53,620 --> 01:03:54,747
No, it's fine.

929
01:03:54,830 --> 01:03:56,457
Nice to meet you.

930
01:03:56,540 --> 01:03:57,750
Hello.

931
01:04:00,878 --> 01:04:01,879
Huh?

932
01:04:02,838 --> 01:04:04,548
Hey! You always eat at my restaurant.

933
01:04:04,673 --> 01:04:06,008
Ma'am!

934
01:04:10,929 --> 01:04:14,391
His father was right.
Humans are the scariest.

935
01:04:22,232 --> 01:04:25,069
THE PRACTICAL GUIDE TO LOVE

936
01:04:31,158 --> 01:04:33,660
IT'S ALREADY TOO LATE

937
01:04:34,703 --> 01:04:37,581
THE BIGGEST PROJECT OF HIS LIFE!

938
01:04:38,540 --> 01:04:41,502
CAN'T STOP BEING NOSY AROUND YOU

939
01:04:46,757 --> 01:04:49,259
I'M GLAD WE MET NOW

940
01:04:50,177 --> 01:04:53,055
THE MEANING OF YOU

941
01:04:53,639 --> 01:04:55,933
SHOULD I TURN OFF THE LIGHTS?

942
01:04:57,976 --> 01:04:59,645
Dating is different now.

943
01:05:00,104 --> 01:05:02,523
In our 20s,
it was just about us two being in love.

944
01:05:03,524 --> 01:05:04,900
Oh, gosh!

945
01:05:04,983 --> 01:05:06,735
Man, I can't stop thinking about it.

946
01:05:06,860 --> 01:05:08,570
If you aren't pretending to read the book
while spying on me

947
01:05:08,654 --> 01:05:09,863
why are you still reading
the table of contents?

948
01:05:09,988 --> 01:05:12,783
Your mom seems to be curious
about how things are going with Ui-yeong.

949
01:05:14,576 --> 01:05:16,745
People will want to know about you
once the news is out.

950
01:05:17,079 --> 01:05:18,997
Reporters will chase you everywhere, too.

951
01:05:19,331 --> 01:05:20,332
Move abroad for school.

952
01:05:20,416 --> 01:05:22,126
Whatever it is...

953
01:05:22,209 --> 01:05:24,545
Stand for what you love.

954
01:05:25,129 --> 01:05:26,255
I want

955
01:05:27,214 --> 01:05:28,465
to fall in love with you.

956
01:05:34,847 --> 01:05:36,849
Subtitles by: Min-sun Kim
